TAMPA -- Visitors to downtown Tampa on Friday, Oct. 9 will have a unique vantage point to see the city as a zipline across Franklin Street as part of a FitLife Foods promotion. 
Two ziplines will be placed on Franklin Street spanning from Madison and Zack Streets. 
Franklin Street will also be closed from 11 a.m. to 7 p.m. 
Event promoters promise zipline races, skill events and can accommodate up to 1000 riders, weather permitting. Also included in the promotion are a rock climbing wall and information about FitLife Foods. 
The cost of ziplining is $10 per ride and to use the rock climbing wall is $10. For the adventurous types who want to do both activities, it's $15. Read or Share this story: http://on.wtsp.com/1Rn0JEP More Stories
